    "Document-oriented databasePatient EMRs obtained from different hospitals are encrypted with a symmetric encryption algorithm and are kept distributed in the document-oriented database.Although patients are the owners of their EMRs, they cannot make changes to their data, but they can only authorize or remove access if requested.",
    "Each EMR of the patient is divided into a different number of fragments according to its sensitivity.",
    "The fragments can be of any data type such as text, file, image, video, and pdf.",
    "A symmetric key is generated for each fragment, and the Fig. 3 Proposed scheme architecture fragment is encrypted with its symmetric key and stored in the document-oriented database.",
    "In the database, apart from patient EMRs, the data resulting from the analysis of these EMRs by third entities are kept encrypted with a newly generated symmetric key."
